        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/larry_link/{size}/1312_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-26T04:49:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=1186848\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2010 Fran\u00e7ois Raveneau Chablis 1er Cru Butteaux</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Chablis, Chablis 1er Cru (10/25/2018)</em><br>\nPopped and poured. Amazing nose of lemon, honey, sea brine and spice. The palate is rich, lemony with a lithe texture that has layers of complexity, then finishes with a bitter lemon rind element that is lifting. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
