      {
        "id": 2511812,
        "name": "Larry Link",
        "username": "Larry_Link",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/larry_link/{size}/1312_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-30T05:34:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"146791\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>had 08 Butteaux last night. A disappointment in the context of the 10 and 04. A bit dilute and lacking vibrant acidity, though smelled nice and had decent fruit. Not Chablis in character, more generic.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Your note echos a note I posted to CT on the 2008 Butteaux a couple of years ago:</p>\n<p>6/17/2016 rated 89 points: Iodine infused, citrusy nose. Somewhat dilute and thin on the palate, a little watery and simple compared to other 08 Rav\u2019s that I have consumed in the past. Not a ton of energy and lift either, although as it warmed it started to show some lifting bitter elements on the finish that added some complexity. (2617 views)</p>",
